the creation of leaf entity nodes, which is handled by the Partition3D class.</p><p class="javadoc">See:</p><div class="indent inline-content"><p>away3d.partition.EntityNode</p></div><div class="indent inline-content"><p>away3d.partition.Partition3D</p></div><div class="indent inline-content"><p>away3d.containers.Scene3D</p></div></div></div><h3 class="section">Constructor</h3><div class="fields"><div class="field "><a name="new"></a><h3><p><code><a href="#new"><span class="identifier">new</span></a> ()</code></p></h3><div class="doc"><p>Creates a new NodeBase object.</p></div></div></div><h3 class="section">Variables</h3><div class="fields"><div class="field "><a name="parent"></a><h3><p><code><span class="label">read only</span><a href="../../../away3d/core/partition/NodeBase.html#parent"><span class="identifier">parent</span></a>:<a class="type" title="The NodeBase class is an abstract base class for any type of space partition tree node." href="../../../away3d/core/partition/NodeBase.html">NodeBase</a></code></p></h3><div class="doc"><p></p></div></div><div class="field "><a name="showDebugBounds"></a><h3><p><code><a href="../../../away3d/core/partition/NodeBase.html#showDebugBounds"><span class="identifier">showDebugBounds</span></a>:<span class="type">Bool</span></code></p></h3><div class="doc"><p></p></div></div></div><h3 class="section">Methods</h3><div class="fields"><div class="field "><a name="acceptTraverser"></a><h3><p><code><a href="#acceptTraverser"><span class="identifier">acceptTraverser</span></a> (<span style="white-space:nowrap">traverser:<a class="type" title="IPartitionTraverser is a hierarchical visitor pattern that traverses through a Partition3D data structure." href="../../../away3d/core/traverse/PartitionTraverser.html">PartitionTraverser</a></span>):<span class="type">Void</span></code></p></h3><div class="doc"><p>Allows the traverser to visit the current node. If the traverser's enterNode method returns true, the
traverser will be sent down the child nodes of the tree.
This method should be overridden if the order of traversal is important (such as for BSP trees) - or if static
